&lt;h1 id="submit-to-an-appropriate-journal"&gt;Submit to an appropriate journal&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Few, but ripe.&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Friedrich_Gauss"&gt;Carl Friedrich Gauss&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is always tempting to submit a paper to a prestigious journal, but if the paper makes only a borderline case for publication in this journal, then the net result may be a lengthy process, critical reviews holding the paper to a very high standard, and ultimate rejection of the paper.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Use the introduction to “sell” the key points of your paper</title><link>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/en/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 20:13:57 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/en/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
