&lt;h1 id="use-the-introduction-to-sell-the-key-points-of-your-paper"&gt;Use the introduction to &amp;ldquo;sell&amp;rdquo; the key points of your paper&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rule to live by: I won&amp;rsquo;t use anything I can&amp;rsquo;t explain in five minutes.
— Philip Crosby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every now and then as editor, I see an author upset at a rejection of a paper because the referee &amp;ldquo;clearly did not grasp the key point of the paper&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Submit a final draft, not a first draft</title><link>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 20:13:18 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/en/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/terencetao/writing-guide/zh/submit-a-final-draft-not-a-first-draft.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
